## Definition of Commercial Use

"Commercial use" includes but is not limited to:
- Selling the Software or derivative works
- Offering the Software as a paid service (SaaS, hosting, etc.)
- Using the Software to generate revenue directly or indirectly
- Incorporating the Software into commercial products
- Using the Software in a business context for profit

